headline: What Catalysts Are Rewriting The Story For Arthur J. Gallagher (AJG)?
summary: Why Gallagher’s Trimmed Price Target Matters Arthur J. Gallagher’s fair value estimate has been nudged down from about US$293.56 to US$288.50, a small adjustment that still reflects meaningful shifts in how analysts are thinking about the stock. Behind this, revenue growth assumptions have been toned down as some analysts factor in softer organic growth, a cooling phase in the P&C insurance cycle, and near term earnings that several firms describe as “bumpy,” while others still see room for...
